---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Issues | Dana Tovar for Smithville City Council">
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h1>What I Stand For</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Real solutions for Smithville's most important issues.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="issues-section section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="issues-grid">
        
        <!-- Issue 1 -->
        <article class="issue-card">
          <div class="issue-content">
            <h2>Managing Growth Responsibly</h2>
            <div class="local-context">
              <span class="context-label">Local Context:</span> Smithville has grown ~10% since 2020. The Domain Industrial Park is under development at HWY 71 and SH 95. New residents are arriving daily.
            </div>
            <p><strong>My Position:</strong> Growth is good when it is guided. Residents should have a seat at the table when development decisions are made. Transparency means you see the plans before the bulldozers arrive.</p>
            <div class="action-item">
              <strong>Action:</strong> Require developer town halls for major zoning changes.
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Issue 2 -->
        <article class="issue-card">
          <div class="issue-content">
            <h2>Preserving Smithville's Character</h2>
            <div class="local-context">
              <span class="context-label">Local Context:</span> We are a "Film Friendly" city, a Cultural District, and a "Music Friendly" community, part of the First Street Initiative.
            </div>
            <p><strong>My Position:</strong> Our history and culture are economic assets, not obstacles. Smart growth means building the future without demolishing what makes Smithville worth living in.</p>
            <div class="action-item">
              <strong>Action:</strong> Support downtown revitalization while protecting historical corridors.
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Issue 3 -->
        <article class="issue-card">
          <div class="issue-content">
            <h2>Infrastructure and Services</h2>
            <div class="local-context">
              <span class="context-label">Local Context:</span> Southeast Drainage Improvements are ongoing, and solid waste services recently transitioned to Texas Disposal Systems.
            </div>
            <p><strong>My Position:</strong> Transparent budgeting so residents know exactly where infrastructure dollars go. Accessible communication when projects affect your street or your commute.</p>
            <div class="action-item">
              <strong>Action:</strong> Create a public, easy-to-read "Project Dashboard" for all city infrastructure work.
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Issue 4 -->
        <article class="issue-card">
          <div class="issue-content">
            <h2>Supporting Local Business</h2>
            <div class="local-context">
              <span class="context-label">Local Context:</span> Smithville's Main Street economy and the Chamber of Commerce are the lifeblood of our town.
            </div>
            <p><strong>My Position:</strong> A council member who shows up, listens to business owners, and fights for policies that help small businesses thrive, not just big developers.</p>
            <div class="action-item">
              <strong>Action:</strong> Streamline permitting for local small businesses to open and expand faster.
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Issue 5 -->
        <article class="issue-card">
          <div class="issue-content">
            <h2>Property Taxes & Fiscal Responsibility</h2>
            <div class="local-context">
              <span class="context-label">Local Context:</span> With affordability continuing to be a major concern, keeping costs reasonable is crucial for families.
            </div>
            <p><strong>My Position:</strong> Every dollar the city spends should be justified in plain language. Transparency is a budget line you can read and understand clearly.</p>
            <div class="action-item">
              <strong>Action:</strong> Publish single-page, plain-English budget summaries every quarter.
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Issue 6 -->
        <article class="issue-card">
          <div class="issue-content">
            <h2>Parks, Quality of Life, and Community</h2>
            <div class="local-context">
              <span class="context-label">Local Context:</span> Our 11 city parks, Riverbend Park, and proximity to state parks are incredible assets.
            </div>
            <p><strong>My Position:</strong> Accessible public spaces are what make Smithville feel like home. Maintaining and improving them is not optional; it's essential for our families.</p>
            <div class="action-item">
              <strong>Action:</strong> Secure grant funding specifically for local park maintenance and improvements.
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="call-to-action-section">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2>Let's talk about the issues.</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">I want to hear what matters most to you.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-outline btn-large">Contact Dana</a>
      <a href="/get-involved#yard-sign" class="btn btn-primary btn-large" style="margin-left: 1rem;">Get a Yard Sign</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    padding: 6rem 0;
  }
  
  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  
  .text-center {
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .issues-section {
    background-color: var(--color-background);
  }
  
  .issues-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .issue-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    overflow: hidden;
    border-top: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
  }
  
  .issue-content {
    padding: 2.5rem;
  }
  
  .issue-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }
  
  .local-context {
    background-color: #F1F5F9;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #475569;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
  }
  
  .context-label {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  
  .issue-content p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .action-item {
    background-color: rgba(184, 66, 51, 0.05);
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(184, 66, 51, 0.2);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  
  .action-item strong {
    color: var(--color-highlight);
  }
  
  .call-to-action-section {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background-color: white;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(27, 58, 92, 0.1);
  }
  
  .btn-large {
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .issue-content {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
    
    .call-to-action-section .btn {
      display: block;
      margin: 0.5rem auto !important;
      max-width: 300px;
    }
  }
</style>
